Photo by Italy • Travel • Passion in Fontana Di Trevi-Roma. May be an image of one or more people, people standing and The Trevi Fountain.

node.text:
▪ The famous Trevi Fountain is one of the symbols of Rome. A few interesting facts: the fountain was built in a baroque style and is the largest fountain in the city. It adheres to the wall of the Poli Palace and is 27 meters high. The figure in the central part is Okeanos/Neptune - the god of freshwater and the sea. There is a custom of throwing coins into the fountain for good luck, and therefore every day (let's agree, before 👑) a lot of coins went to the fountain, which was collected at night and later donated to charities. The fountain was made famous by Federico Fellini's film "La Dolce Vita", one of the scenes was shot in this fountain (who watched the movie? 😉), which later inspired many people to bathe and walk through the fountain in the middle of the night like film characters. Now, however, all bathing and entering the water is prohibited. Do you know any other interesting facts related to this place? 😊⁣
